Darekia is a genus of stem group Neoptera which is due to be published by Acta Palaeontologica Polonica. It existed in what is now Poland, during the upper Carboniferous period. It was described by Jakub Prokop, Wieslaw Krzemiński, Ewa Krzemińska, and Dariusz Wojciechowski in 2011, and the type species is Darekia sanguinea.